Researchers from Max Planck Institute for Informatics, MIT and Google have developed DragGAN.

It lets you 'drag' any part of a picture to exactly where you want it.

DragGAN has two main parts:

â€¢ Motion supervision â€” this guides the point you're moving towards the target position

Where Photoshop often requires intricate skill and knowledge, DragGAN makes complex edits as simple as drag and drop.

There are four types of Artificial Intelligence: Reactive machines, limited memory, theory of mind and self awareness.
 Beginning with Reactive Machines : This type of AI performs basic operations.

 This level of AI is the simplest. A machine Learning that takes a human face as an input and output a box around the face to identify it as a face is a simple, reactive machine.

Although static machine models are reactive machines. These models can be downloaded, traded, passed around into developer's tool kit with ease. Going to Limited Memory that have the ability to store previous Data in order to make better predictions.
 With limited memory, machine learning architecture becomes a little more complex.

Concerning the theory of mind, it can be seen in things like self-driving cars. In other words, in this type, AI begins to interact with the thoughts and emotions of humans.
 Finishing with self awareness, this type of AI exists only in stories, and as stories often do, instills both immense amounts of hope and fear into audiences. Here we're talking about independent intelligence beyond human.

 To conclude, AI is a strong software tool for the future that's here to stay. It's eliminating repetitive tasks in the workforce and elevating humans to reach higher selves, embracing constant states of change and creativity.
